<dl id="n25066c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25066c">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25066c"> 66(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> in sleep &lsquo;Self&rsquo; leaves / Soma</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Obviously that belief lies at the base of the argument by which Herbert Spencer, Tylor, and others of their school show how theories of the soul and future life were elaborated from barbaric conceptions of <mark>the &lsquo;other self&rsquo; which quitted the body for a time in sleep and dreams</mark> and swoons, leaving it at death to return no more <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14038g" href="c14all.htm#c14038g">VI.C.14:038(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
